{"lemma": "صُوفٌ", "slug": "صُوفٌ", "root": "ص.#.ف", "root_slug": "ص-_-ف", "root_link": "/words/roots/ص-_-ف", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 3, "pos_tags": ["noun", "verb"], "has_etymology": false, "sense_count": 6}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n25226"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D9%8F%D9%88%D9%81%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "wool", "fa": "پشم", "ur": "اون", "tr": "yün", "id": "wol", "bn": "উল", "es": "lana", "fr": "laine", "de": "Wolle", "ru": "шерсть", "zh": "羊毛"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "wool", "tags": ["collective"]}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to produce wool, to increase its wool (of sheep, etc.)"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to produce wool, to increase its wool (of sheep, etc.)"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to make someone Sufi"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to have cotton-like fungus (see the image) (of plants)"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to decay (to have wool-like fungus)", "tags": ["intransitive"]}]}, "etymology": null, "ipa": ["/sˤuːf/", "/sˤawf/", "/sˤa.wi.fa/", "/sˤaw.wa.fa/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n25226", "headword_ar": "صُوفٌ", "root": "Swf", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Wool;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "an appertenance of sheep,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(in the S"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lil$~aApi", "text_ar": "لِلشَّاةِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in the M"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "liloganami", "text_ar": "لِلْغَنَمِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and in the O and Msb [more definitely]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lilD~aA^oni", "text_ar": "لِلضَّاْنِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "which is to them like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$aEarN", "text_ar": "شَعَرٌ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to goats and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wabarN", "text_ar": "وَبَرٌ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to camels:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M:) [in the K only said to be well know:] n. un."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SuwfapN", "text_ar": "صُوفَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (M,) [i. e.] this latter has a more particular signification [meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a portion, flock, tuft,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "wisp, of wool"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (S, O, Msb, K:) and sometimes"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SuwfN", "text_ar": "صُوفٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is used in the sense of the n. un., as mentioned by Sb: (M:) the pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SuwfN", "text_ar": "صُوفٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aSowaAfN", "text_ar": "اَصْوَافٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sorts of wool"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (M:) and the dim. of the n. un. is ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SuwayofapN", "text_ar": "صُوَيْفَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) One says"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xaroqaA='u wajadato SuwfFA", "text_ar": "خَرْقَا=ءُ وَجَدَتْ صُوفًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "An unskilful woman that has found wool"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (As, O, K:) a prov. (As, O) relating to property possessed by such as does not deserve to have it: (As, TA:) because the unskilful woman, when she lights upon wool, mars it, (O, K,) not spinning it well: (O:) applied to the stupid person who finds property and wastes it; (O, K;) or to him who finds that of which he knows not the value, and wastes it. (Z, TA.) And one says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fulaAnN yalobasu AlS~uwfa waAlquTona", "text_ar": "فُلَانٌ يَلْبَسُ الصُّوفَ وَالقُطْنَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Such a one wears what is made of wool and of cotton."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A, TA.) In the saying of a poet,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "HalobaAnapK rakobaAnapK Safuwfi\n                      \n                     \n                        taxoliTu bayona wabarK waSuwfi"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Of one that is milked and ridden, that yields a row of bowls of her milk,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(but see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SafuwfN", "text_ar": "صَفُوفٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", of which other explanations have been given,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that mingles camels' fur and wool"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], the latter hemistich means, as Th says, accord. to IAar, that is sold, and with the price whereof are purchased camels and sheep: or, accord. to As, that is quick in her pace; the drawing back of her fore legs being likened to [the motion of] the bow of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "nad~aAf", "text_ar": "نَدَّاف"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "who mixes camels' fur and wool. (M.) One says also,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^axa*otu biSuwfi raqabatihi", "text_ar": "اَخَذْتُ بِصُوفِ رَقَبَتِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, M, K, but in the M"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^axa*a", "text_ar": "اَخَذَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "biSuwfatihaA", "text_ar": "بِصُوفَتِهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, O) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "biSaAfihaA", "text_ar": "بِصَافِهَا", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (M, K,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "biTuwfi raqabatihi", "text_ar": "بِطُوفِ رَقَبَتِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "biTaAfihaA", "text_ar": "بِطَافِهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "biZuwfi zaqabatihi", "text_ar": "بِظُوفِ زَقَبَتِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "biZaAfihaA", "text_ar": "بِظَافِهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "biquwfi raqabatihi", "text_ar": "بِقُوفِ رَقَبَتِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "biqaAfihaA", "text_ar": "بِقَافِهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, O,) meaning (tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I laid hold upon"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the pendent hair in the hollow of the back of his neck:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IDrd, S, M, O, K:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the downy hairs upon the back of his neck:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, O:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the skin of his neck:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IAar, S, O, K:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the back of his neck, altogether:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Fr, S, O, K:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I took him by force:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Abu-l-Ghowth, S, O, K:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I followed him, thinking that I should not reach him, and overtook him;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and this one says whether he lay hold upon his neck or not. (Abu-s-Semeyda', S, O, K.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aEoTaAhu biSuwfi", "text_ar": "اَعْطَاهُ بِصُوفِ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "raqabatihi", "text_ar": "رَقَبَتِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He gave it altogether"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aEoTaAhu birum~atihi", "text_ar": "اَعْطَاهُ بِرُمَّتِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": or (as expl. by A' Obeyd, S, O)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he gave it gratuitously; not taking a price."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, O, K.) ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Suwfu AlbaHori", "text_ar": "صُوفُ البَحْرِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[lit."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The wool of the sea"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] is"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a thing"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "substance"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in the form of the animal"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Suwf", "text_ar": "صُوف"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e.,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of wool;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "evidently meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sea-weed resembling wool;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "such as is found in abundance thrown up on the beaches of the Red Sea: and that this is generally, if not in every instance, meant by the identical Hebrew word"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "סוּף", "text_ar": "סוּף", "orth_type": "plain"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", as used in the Bible, has been most satisfactorily shown in art. “ Red Sea ” (by my deeply-lamented nephew Edward Stanley Poole) in Dr. William Smith's “ Dictionary of the Bible ”]: it is said in one of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^abadiy~aAt", "text_ar": "اَبَدِيَّات"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", [see art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Abd", "text_ar": "ابد"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA A=tiyka maA bal~a", "text_ar": "لَا ا=تِيكَ مَا بَلَّ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baHorN SuwfapF", "text_ar": "بَحْرٌ صُوفَةً"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I will not come to thee as long as a sea wets a portion of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Suwf", "text_ar": "صُوف"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], or, as Lh relates it,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA bal~a AlbaHoru Suwfahu", "text_ar": "مَا بَلَّ البَحْرُ صُوفَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "as long as the sea wets its"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Suwf", "text_ar": "صُوف"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; meaning,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "ever"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (M, TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["M", "S", "O", "Msb", "K", "As", "TA", "IDrd", "IAar", "Fr"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}